cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CV 

This paper discusses privacy-preserving mechanisms in machine learning environments, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper focuses on differential privacy and data privacy. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses the application of privacy-preserving mechanisms in machine learning. The third likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper discusses the use of noise to protect data privacy. The fourth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper discusses the use of wavelet transforms to embed noise into data. The fifth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper discusses the application of privacy-preserving mechanisms in image processing.
